press_freedom: critical journalists and bloggers are threatened and arrested, leading news sites are blocked, access to information is restricted, and media is diversity is unknown. the president of belarus since 1994 is alexander lukashenko.  he is independent and supported by the belaya rus, a big tent organization formed to support the president; however, belaya rus is not a political party. while the president is supposedly non-partisan, his primary support comes from left-leaning parties such as the communist party of belarus (kpb), the liberal democratic party of belarus, and the agrarian party. opposition parties include the party of the belarusian popular front (bpf), the conservative-christian party, and the right-of-center united civic party.
